<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[189,310,1559,1585]" box="[189,310,1559,1585]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1559,1585]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1559,1585]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[189,1399,1605,1738]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
This species is similar in shape, sculpture and often color to 
<taxonomicName authority="Samuelson &amp; Biondi, 2016" authorityName="Samuelson &amp; Biondi" authorityYear="2016" box="[921,1108,1606,1632]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Arsipoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gomezzuritai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[921,1108,1606,1632]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">A. gomezzuritai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1117,1209,1606,1632]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gomez-Zurita" authorityYear="2010" box="[1270,1398,1606,1632]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Arsipoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rostrata">
<emphasis box="[1270,1398,1606,1632]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">A. rostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[197,323,1640,1667]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[288,1299,265,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[288,1300,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 2. Habitus. A. Arsipoda longifrons sp. nov, Humboldt S track. B. A. montana sp. nov, Mt Humboldt. C. A. paniensis sp. nov, Mt Panié. D. A. povilaensis sp. nov, Pic d’Amoa. E. A. punctata sp. nov., Mueo. F. A. rostrata Gómez-Zurita, 2010, Koghi Mts. G. A. rutai sp. nov, Poro Plateau. H. A. shirleyae Samuelson, 1973, S Humboldt. I. A. transversa sp. nov., Mt Koghi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840412/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Figs 2A, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[335,372,1641,1667]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,1299,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1399,1299,1926]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus. A. Arsipoda wanati sp. nov, Mt Humboldt. B. A. yiambiae Samuelson, 1973, Yiambi. C. A. gomezzuritai sp. nov., Dzumac Mts." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840414/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">3C</figureCitation>
). They are distinguishable from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1842" box="[818,926,1641,1667]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Arsipoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[818,926,1641,1667]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Arsipoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the elongate antennae (LAN/ LB: ³ Ż 0.70, 
<specimenCount box="[362,384,1676,1702]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
generally Ż 0.60) and the elongate frons with narrow frontal carina. The three species can be reliably distinguished by the shape of genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[835,967,1711,1737]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[237,1351,265,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[237,1351,265,1820]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 9. Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral (l), ventral (v) and dorsal (d) view. A. Arsipoda isola Samuelson, 1973, Bois du Sud. B. A. longifrons sp. nov., Humboldt S track. C. A. montana sp. nov., Mt Humboldt. D. A. paniensis sp. nov., Mt Panié. E. A. povilaensis sp. nov., Pic d’Amoa, Povila. F. A. punctata sp. nov., Mueo. G. A. rostrata Gómez-Zurita, 2010, Koghi Mts. H. A. rutai sp. nov. Poro Plateau. I. A. shirleyae Samuelson, 1973, S Humboldt." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840427/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Figs 9B, G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[979,1032,1711,1737]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,735,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,735,1855]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 10. Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral (l), ventral (v) and dorsal (d) view. A. Arsipoda transversa sp. nov., Mt Koghi. B. A. wanati sp. nov., Mt Humboldt. C. A. yiambiae Samuelson, 1973, Yiambi. D. A. gomezzuritai sp. nov., Dzumac Mts. E. Nomenclature. Abbreviations: amt = apical median tooth; apr = apical process; bp = basal part; dl = dorsal ligula; vs = ventral sulcus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840429/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">10D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1044,1157,1711,1738]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="42.[189,232,1649,1675]" captionTargetBox="[242,1360,277,1603]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[220,1367,265,1610]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Fig. 11. Female genitalia. A–S. Spermatheca. A. Arsipoda agalma Samuelson, 1973, N of Pic Vincent. B. A. atra sp. nov., Aoupinié. C. A. communis sp. nov., Dzumac Mts. D. A. doboszi sp. nov., Mt Do. E. A.elongata sp. nov., Mt Humboldt. F. A. evax Samuelson, 1973, Chagrin. G. A. geographica Gómez- Zurita, 2010, Mt Humboldt. H. A. gressitti sp. nov., Farino. I. A. isola Samuelson, 1973, Bois du Sud. J. A. longifrons sp. nov., Humboldt S track. K. A. paniensis sp. nov., Mt Panie. L. A. povilaensis sp. nov., Pic d’Amoa, Povila.M. A. rostrata Gómez-Zurita, 2010, Dzumac Road.N. A. rutai sp. nov.Dzumac Road. O. A. shirleyae Samuelson, 1973, Haute Rivière Bleue. P. A. transversa sp. nov., Mt Koghi. Q. A. wanati sp. nov., Mt Humboldt. R. A. yiambiae Samuelson, 1973, Yiambi. S. A. gomezzuritai sp. nov., Dzumac Mts. T. Tignum (t) and vaginal palpi (vp) of A. communis sp. nov., Mt Do. Abbreviations: a = appendix; ap = apical part; bp = basal part; c = collum or neck; d = ductus; LSPc = length of spermathecal capsule; SPc = spermathecal capsule = ap + c + bp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840431/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">11J, M, S</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
